	Mon Sep 29 22:36:26 IST 1997

	http://www.odyssey.co.il/~heksterb/Software/afpfs


I haven't yet begun collecting and collating an exhaustive list of
all bugs and limitations in AFPFS;  for the time being I'm just
adding things as they come to mind.


Zone look-ups probably don't work yet-- I haven't tested it because I
don't have access to a Mac in a multiple zone-network.  Specifying the
zone numerically is probably most likely to work.

I don't deal at all yet with resource forks or creator signatures/file
types.  Since these concepts don't have any meaning on the Linux side
their absence will not affect you on this side, but files created on the
Macintosh though afpfs will be affected.  Any solution for creator/types
will probably involve file extensions.  A solution for resource forks
may be found in the `.AppleDouble' directory mechanism.

I am also considering how best to implement CR/LF translation for text files.

I'm not doing any mapping of user names yet-- all files and directories
are made owned by the user who performed the mount.  This is actually
fairly logical.

I realize now that some, if not all, of the protocols should have been
implemented as kernel-level protocols.  That is, it should be possible
to open an ASP socket using the socket(2) system call.  I will most
likely change the implementation to do things this way.

There is no documentation for the AppleTalk protocol implementation APIs.
Does anybody think this would be useful?

I also haven't looked hard at simultaneously mounting multiple volumes
from the same server.
